Crystal Palace caretaker boss Keith Millen has said the texts between Malky Mackay and Iain Moody are ‘hard to justify’.

Moody resigned from Palace as sporting director in the wake of the allegations on Thursday.

Mackay was close to be being named Palace boss before Sportsmail’s extraordinary revelations regarding discriminatory texts between the pair. 

