Speaking ahead of his side’s London derby against West Ham, Millen said: ‘I don’t want to get involved in the texts. That sort of language is not something you hear in football time. It’s hard to justify if it’s true.

'I had a chat with them (the players) about being focused. They have been through a lot of things together.

'He (Moody) was brought in to scout so the chairman will have to look at that situation and I've spoken to the chairman and that will remain private.'

And Millen was coy about the managerial situation at the club, although he insists he would be willing to have a crack at it. 

